{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.41",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 41,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 41",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 41 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:1",
      "text": "Canst thou draw out leviathan with an hook? or his tongue with a cord which thou lettest down?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:2",
      "text": "Canst thou put an hook into his nose? or bore his jaw through with a thorn?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:3",
      "text": "Will he make many supplications unto thee? will he speak soft words unto thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:4",
      "text": "Will he make a covenant with thee? wilt thou take him for a servant for ever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:5",
      "text": "Wilt thou play with him as with a bird? or wilt thou bind him for thy maidens?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:6",
      "text": "Shall the companions make a banquet of him? shall they part him among the merchants?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:7",
      "text": "Canst thou fill his skin with barbed irons? or his head with fish spears?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:8",
      "text": "Lay thine hand upon him, remember the battle, do no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:9",
      "text": "Behold, the hope of him is in vain: shall not one be cast down even at the sight of him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:10",
      "text": "None is so fierce that dare stir him up: who then is able to stand before me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:11",
      "text": "Who hath prevented me, that I should repay him? whatsoever is under the whole heaven is mine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:12",
      "text": "I will not conceal his parts, nor his power, nor his comely proportion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:13",
      "text": "Who can discover the face of his garment? or who can come to him with his double bridle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:14",
      "text": "Who can open the doors of his face? his teeth are terrible round about.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:15",
      "text": "His scales are his pride, shut up together as with a close seal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:16",
      "text": "One is so near to another, that no air can come between them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:17",
      "text": "They are joined one to another, they stick together, that they cannot be sundered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:18",
      "text": "By his neesings a light doth shine, and his eyes are like the eyelids of the morning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:19",
      "text": "Out of his mouth go burning lamps, and sparks of fire leap out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:20",
      "text": "Out of his nostrils goeth smoke, as out of a seething pot or caldron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:21",
      "text": "His breath kindleth coals, and a flame goeth out of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:22",
      "text": "In his neck remaineth strength, and sorrow is turned into joy before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:23",
      "text": "The flakes of his flesh are joined together: they are firm in themselves; they cannot be moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:24",
      "text": "His heart is as firm as a stone; yea, as hard as a piece of the nether millstone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:25",
      "text": "When he raiseth up himself, the mighty are afraid: by reason of breakings they purify themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:26",
      "text": "The sword of him that layeth at him cannot hold: the spear, the dart, nor the habergeon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:27",
      "text": "He esteemeth iron as straw, and brass as rotten wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:28",
      "text": "The arrow cannot make him flee: slingstones are turned with him into stubble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:29",
      "text": "Darts are counted as stubble: he laugheth at the shaking of a spear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:30",
      "text": "Sharp stones are under him: he spreadeth sharp pointed things upon the mire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:31",
      "text": "He maketh the deep to boil like a pot: he maketh the sea like a pot of ointment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:32",
      "text": "He maketh a path to shine after him; one would think the deep to be hoary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:33",
      "text": "Upon earth there is not his like, who is made without fear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.41.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:34",
      "text": "He beholdeth all high things: he is a king over all the children of pride.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
